32. Write a Java program that accepts two floating point numbers and checks whether they are the same up to two decimal places.
/*check if up to 2d.p. same: Math.abs(num1 - num2) <= 0.01*/

import java.util.Scanner;
public class Exercise32 {

public static void main(String[] args) { 
 Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in); 
 System.out.print("Input first floating足point number: "); 
 double num1 = input.nextDouble(); 
 System.out.print("Input second floating足point number: "); 
 double num2 = input.nextDouble(); 
 input.close(); 
  
 if (Math.abs(num1 - num2) <= 0.01) { 
     System.out.println("These numbers are the same."); 
 } 
 else { 
     System.out.println("These numbers are different."); 
 } 
    } 
}

>>
Input first floating足point number: 1235                                                                       
Input second floating足point number: 2534                                                                      
These numbers are different. 
